umbai Bagh|last=Shantha|first=Sukanya|date=11 February 2020|website=The Wire|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref><ref name=\":19\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/news/india/mumbai-police-commissioner-param-bir-singh-takes-over|title='Won't Allow Delhi-Like Violence': New Mumbai Police Commissioner|last=Sinha|first=Ankita|date=2020-03-04|website=The Quint|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref>\n|-\n|YMCA ground, Agripada\n|17 January 2020\n|Yes\n|{{Age in years and days|month1=1|day1=17|year1=2020|month2=3|day2=4|year2=2020}} on 4 Mar\n|<ref name=\"MumProtestYMCA\" /><ref name=\":19\" />\n|-\n|Malerkotla, Punjab\n|Anaj Mandi\n|9 January 2020\n|Yes\n|{{Age in years and days|month1=1|day1=9|year1=2020|month2=2|day2=20|year2=2020}} on 20 Feb\t\n|<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ghazali |first1=Mohammed |last2=Dey |first2=Stela |title=Punjab's Biggest Anti-Citizenship Law Protest Held In Malerkotla |url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/punjabs-biggest-anti-citizenship-law-protest-held-in-malerkotla-2182815 |accessdate=21 February 2020 |work=The NDTV |date=20 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|Ranchi, Jharkhand\n|Haj House\n|19/20 January 2020\n|No\n|{{Age in years and days|month1=1|day1=19|year1=2020|month2=3|day2=21|year2=2020}} on 21 March\t\n|<ref>{{cite news |title=Unhindered, Ranchi's 'Shaheen Bagh' completes 1 month |url=https://www.dailypioneer.com/2020/state-editions/unhindered--ranchi---s----shaheen-bagh----completes-1-month.html |accessdate=21 February 2020 |work=The Pioneer |date=19 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Kumar |first1=Raj |title=Panic at Jharkhand's Shaheen Bagh |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/jharkhand/panic-at-jharkhands-shaheen-bagh/cid/1742003 |accessdate=21 February 2020 |work=The Telegraph (Calcutta) |date=4 February 2020}}</ref><ref>https://www.hindustantimes.com/cities/two-months-on-ranchi-s-saheen-bagh-stir-suspended-till-april-5/story-iySb1fqguqmnKCgE4dUtgJ.html</ref>\n| Suspended till 5th April due to [[coronavirus pandemic]]\n|-\n|Deoband, Uttar Pradesh\n|Idgah ground\n|27 January 2020\n|Yes\n|{{Age in years and days|month1=1|day1=27|year1=2020|month2=2|day2=6|year2=2020}} on 6 Feb\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/rights/anti-caa-protest-up-deoband|title='There Is No Going Back': Women Lead Shaheen Bagh-Style Protest in UP's Deoband|last=Shantha|first=Sukanya|date=6 February 2020|website=The Wire|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref>\n|-\n|Prayagraj, Uttar Pradesh\n|Mansoor Ali Park \n|12 January 2020\n|Yes\n|{{Age in years and days|month1=1|day1=12|year1=2020|month2=1|day2=25|year2=2020}} on 25 Jan\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/allahabad/cold-no-bar-for-protesters-at-roshan-bagh/articleshow/73593589.cms|title=Cold no bar for protesters at Roshan Bagh|last=|first=|date=25 January 2020|website=The Times of India|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://janataweekly.org/shaheen-bagh-inspired-protests-spread-across-the-country/|title=Shaheen Bagh-Inspired Protests Spread Across the Country \u2013 Janata Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|Gaya, Bihar\n|Shanti Bagh\n|29 December 2019\n|Yes\n|{{Age in years and days|month1=12|day1=29|year1=2019|month2=1|day2=29|year2=2020}} on 29 Jan\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.siasat.com/caa-nrc-gayas-shanti-bagh-turns-mini-shaheen-bagh-1791735/|title=CAA-NRC: Gaya's Shanti Bagh turns into mini Shaheen Bagh|date=2020-01-13|website=The Siasat Daily|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-01-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|Chennai, Tamil Nadu\n|Old Washermanpet\n|14 February 2020\n|No{{Efn|Called off till 31 March due to coronavirus pandemic|name=|group=}}\n|{{Age in years and days|month1=2|day1=14|year1=2020|month2=March|day2=18|year2=2020}} on 18 March\n|<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jayarajan |first1=Sreedevi |title='Will fight any govt that divides us': Women continue Chennai's Shaheen Bagh protest |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/will-fight-any-govt-divides-us-women-continue-chennais-shaheen-bagh-protest-118478 |accessdate=21 February 2020 |work=The News Minute |date=19 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Naig |first1=Udhav |title=Shaheen Bagh-style anti-CAA protest enters day 3 in Chennai |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/shaheen-bagh-style-stirenters-day-3-in-chennai/article30837618.ece |accessdate=21 February 2020 |work=The Hindu |date=17 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theweek.in/news/india/2020/03/18/shaheen-bagh-of-chennai-calls-off-protest-temporarily-due-to-coronavirus-outbreak.html|title=Shaheen Bagh of Chennai 'temporarily' calls off protests amid coronavirus outbreak|last=Subramanian|first=Lakshmi|date=18 March 2020|website=The Week|language=en|others=Web Desk|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n|-\n|Jaffrabad, Delhi\n|[[Jaffrabad, Delhi|Jaffrabad]]\n|\n|Yes\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/women-from-across-country-pledge-support-to-shaheen-bagh-protesters-2192017|title=Women From Across Country Pledge Support To Shaheen Bagh Protesters|last=|first=|date=9 March 2020|website=NDTV|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref>\n|}\nOn 11 January, an all-women sit-in protest started outside Konark Mall in Kondhwa, [[Pune]], organized by Kul Jamaat-e-Tanzeem, an umbrella body of several organisations. This protest started with a few participants and steadily grew a crowd which reached around 500\u2013600 protesters on 19&nbsp;January. According to a protester the movement was to save the constitution and the country. Candle light vigils, human chains and speeches were part of the protest. The venue had banners with slogans such as \"Tumhari Lathi Se Tej Hamari Awaaz Hai\" and \"Liar Liar Desh on Fire\", as well as \"India Needs Education, Jobs, Not CAA, NRC, NPR\".<ref name=\"19 Jan Pune Shaheen\">{{cite news |title=Pune 'Shaheen Bagh in Kondhwa' anti-CAA protest enters ninth day |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/2020/jan/19/pune-shaheen-bagh-in-kondhwa-anti-caa-protest-enters-ninth-day-2091592.html |work=The New Indian Express |date=19 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 January, a group of women started a CAA sit-in demonstration in the market area of Patna's Sabzibagh. Over the following three days, people of all ages gathered to join them in the protest.<ref>{{cite news |title=Slogans of Shaheen Bagh Echo at Patna's Sabzibagh |url=https://thewire.in/women/shaheen-bagh-patna-sabzibagh-caa-protests |accessdate=19 January 2020 |work=The Wire |date=15 January 2020}}</ref> Also on 12 January, inspired by the women of Shaheen Bagh, groups of ten women began sit-in protests at the Mansoor Ali Park of Roshan Bagh, Allahabad.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jafri |first1=Abdul |title=CAA-NRC: Shaheen Bagh-Inspired Protests Spread to Allahabad Via Kanpur |url=https://www.newsclick.in/CAA-NRC-Shaheen-Bagh-Inspired-Protests-Spread-Allahabad-Kanpur |accessdate=19 January 2020 |work=The news Click |date=13 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Anti-CAA stir: Women continue protest on sixth day, offer Friday prayers |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/cities/anti-caa-stir-women-continue-protest-on-sixth-day-offer-friday-prayers/story-jCaU1PUenopo0JsWplKWWO.html |accessdate=19 January 2020 |work=The Hindustan Times |date=17 January 2020}}</ref> Over the next few days, thousands of women, students, and others braved rain and cold to join the resistance against the CAA-NRC through slogans, speeches and poems.<ref>{{cite news |title=Anti CAA protestPrayagraj's mansoor Ali becomes delhi's Shaheen bagh Park |url=http://www.uniindia.com/anti-caa-protests-prayagraj-s-mansoor-ali-park-becomes-delhi-s-shaheen-bagh/north/news/1856557.html |accessdate=19 January 2020 |work=United News of India |date=17 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Protest continues at Roshan Bagh area of Allahabad against CAA, NRC |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/allahabad/protest-continues-at-roshan-bagh-area-of-allahabad-against-caa-nrc/articleshow/73359660.cms |accessdate=19 January 2020 |work=The Times of India |date=18 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nSimilar protests were held at Kanpur's [[Chaman Ganj, Kanpur|Chaman Ganj]], Gaya's Shanti Bagh,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ameen |first1=Faruqh |title=Shaheen Bagh inspires many protests across the country |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/india/shaheen-bagh-inspires-many-protests-across-the-country/cid/1736089 |accessdate=19 January 2020 |work=The Telegraph Calcutta |date=15 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Sameer |title=CAA-NRC: Gaya's Shanti Bagh turns into mini Shaheen Bagh |url=https://www.siasat.com/caa-nrc-gayas-shanti-bagh-turns-mini-shaheen-bagh-1791735/ |accessdate=19 January 2020 |work=The Siasat Daily |date=13 January 2020}}</ref> [[Kota, Rajasthan|Kota]]'s Eidgah ground,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/jaipur/how-can-kota-women-be-behind-say-protesters-after-launching-shaheen-bagh-like-protest-in-city/story-vgy6BhajL1KkwKGVhkf8eL.html|title='How can Kota women be behind?' say protesters after launching Shaheen Bagh-like protest in city|date=2020-01-15|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-01-18}}</ref> Lucknow's [[Husainabad Clock Tower|Clock Tower]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Awasthi |first1=Puja |title=Lucknow's 'Shaheen Bagh': Women start sit-in against CAA at iconic clock tower |url=https://www.theweek.in/news/india/2020/01/18/lucknow-shaheen-bagh-women-start-sit-in-against-caa-at-iconic-clock-tower.html |accessdate=21 January 2020 |work=The Week |date=18 January 2020}}</ref> and [[Fraser Town, Bangalore|Fraser Town]] in Bangalore.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/bangalore/bengaluru-taking-queue-from-shaheen-bagh-women-hold-24-hour-protest-at-frazer-town-6232999/|title=Bengaluru: Taking cue from Shaheen Bagh, women hold 24-hour protest at Frazer Town|last=Arakal|first=Ralph Alex|date=2020-01-24|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref>  Inspired by the Shaheen Bagh protest, a massive anti-CAA-NRC-NPR protest started in Mumbai on 17 January. Around 10,000 women gathered in the evening at the YMCA ground in Mumbai to protest. The protest was organised by NGO collective Mumbai Citizen Quorum.<ref name=\"MumProtestYMCA\">{{cite news |last1=Iyer |first1=Rudrika |title=Mumbai: 10,000 women lend their voice to anti-CAA protest |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/mumbai/mumbai-10000-women-lend-their-voice-to-anti-caa-protest/articleshow/73350759.cms |accessdate=19 January 2020 |work=The Times of India |date=18 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Inspired by Shaheen Bagh, women hold a massive anti-CAA protest at Mumbai's YMCA ground |url=https://indianexpress.com/photos/india-news/inspired-by-shaheen-bagh-women-hold-a-massive-anti-caa-protest-at-mumbais-ymca-ground-6222721/2/ |accessdate=19 January 2020 |work=The Indian Express |date=18 January 2020}}</ref> On 20 January, an indefinite sit-in protest started at Parbhani, called \"Parbhani bhi ek Shaheen Bagh\", which was organised by Samvidhan Bachao Tahrik.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lokmat.com/parabhani/parbhani-protests-against-caa-next-day/amp/|title=CAA protests continued at Parbhani on 2nd day|last=|first=|date=22 January 2020|work=[[Lokmat]]|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"inquilab.com\"/>\n\n== Delhi Assembly election issue ==\nThe blockade at Shaheen Bagh became a campaign issue for the [[2020 Delhi Legislative Assembly election|Delhi Legislative Assembly election]], held on 8&nbsp;February 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/delhi-polls-bjp-doesnt-want-to-open-shaheen-bagh-route-its-doing-dirty-politics-over-this-issue-says-arvind-kejriwal/articleshow/73660231.cms|title=Delhi elections 2020: BJP doesn't want to open Shaheen Bagh route, it's doing dirty politics over this issue, says Arvind Kejriwal|last=|first=|date=27 January 2020|website=The Times of India|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> Chief Minister of Delhi [[Arvind Kejriwal]] [[Aam Aadmi Party]] and Home Minister of India [[Amit Shah]] fiercely criticized each other over their positions on the protest. On 27&nbsp;January, during an election rally, Shah said that the protesters would not listen to the BJP government regarding the removal of the road block. Shah asked Kejriwal whether \"he is with the people of Shaheen Bagh or not\" as some AAP members had publicly sided with the protesters. Kejriwal accused the BJP of using \"dirty politics\" and prolonging the road closures to cause a public backlash against the protesters, and noted their promises to reopen the route following the election meant that they could do so at any time. He urged the BJP leadership to visit Shaheen Bagh, talk with the protesters, and open the blockade.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/gloves-off-cm-arvind-kejriwal-and-amit-shah-attack-each-other-over-shaheen-bagh/articleshow/73678913.cms|title=Gloves off, CM Arvind Kejriwal and Amit Shah attack each other over Shaheen Bagh|last=Mishra|first=Alok KN|date=28 January 2020|website=The Times of India|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Amit Shah dares Kejriwal to visit Shaheen Bagh, asserts Modi govt will not spare anti-nationals|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/national-politics/amit-shah-dares-kejriwal-to-visit-shaheen-bagh-asserts-modi-govt-will-not-spare-anti-nationals-798830.html |accessdate=28 January 2020 |work=The Deccan Herald |date=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nUnion Law Minister [[Ravi Shankar Prasad]] (BJP) said that Shaheen Bagh is offering a platform for the \"anti-India\" gangs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/elections/delhi-assembly-polls-2020/story/can-shaheen-bagh-swing-delhi-assembly-election-1640845-2020-01-28|title=Can Shaheen Bagh swing Delhi Assembly election?|last=Dutta|first=Prabhash K.|date=28 January 2020|website=India Today|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> Junior finance minister [[Parvesh Verma]] (BJP) made hateful and abusive comments about the Shaheen Bagh protesters and claimed that they would be cleared within an hour of the election results being declared on 11 February.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/delhi-election-2020-parvesh-sahib-singh-verma-says-no-shaheen-bagh-protesters-mosques-on-state-land-2170674|title=\"They Will Rape, Kill\": Delhi BJP MP's Shocker On Shaheen Bagh Protesters|last=Dwivedi|first=Sukirti|date=28 January 2020|editor-last=Roy|editor-first=Divyanshu Dutta|website=NDTV|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> Verma was later penalised by the [[Election Commission of India|Election Commission]] and BJP for his comments.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-51276867|title=MPs penalised for comments on peaceful protesters|date=2020-01-29|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-01-29|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\nSeveral other BJP leaders made statements regarding removal of the protesters from Shaheen Bagh. One said that a \"surgical strike\" would be conducted on the protesters on 11 February.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/elections/delhi-assembly-polls-2020/story/tajinder-bagga-bjp-on-shaheen-bagh-1641578-2020-01-30|title=BJP's Tajinder Bagga warns Shaheen Bagh of surgical strike on Feb 11|last=Udayakumar|first=Ganesh Radha|date=30 January 2020|website=India Today|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> [[Hindu Sena]] stated that they would remove all \"Shaheen Bagh Jihadis\" at 11&nbsp;am on 2 February.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/shaheen-bagh-anti-caa-protest-hindu-sena-chief-1641418-2020-01-29|title=Shaheen Bagh 'Jihadis' inciting division of India, will remove them on Feb 2: Hindu Sena|last=Pandey|first=Tanushree|date=29 January 2020|website=India Today|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> This plan was cancelled after consultations with the Delhi Police.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/rights/hindu-sena-shaheen-bagh-protersters|title=Hindu Sena Calls Off Plan to Unleash Violence on Shaheen Bagh Protesters|last=|first=|date=2 February 2020|website=The Wire|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-03}}</ref>\n\n=== Threats to the protesters ===\nSeveral BJP leaders and politicians made hate speeches against the protesters, including [[Yogi Adityanath]], [[Anurag Thakur]] and [[Parvesh Verma]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/man-fires-bullets-in-shaheen-bagh-area/articleshow/73843412.cms|title=Man fires two rounds in air in Shaheen Bagh area; taken into custody.|date=1 February 2020|work=The Times of India|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.in/entry/anurag-thakur-goli-maro-chants-at-delhi-election-rally_in_5e2f9a7bc5b68f86c8cd03b5|title=Anurag Thakur On 'Goli Maro' Chants At Poll Rally: 'People Reacted. What Can I Do?|last1=Sebastian|first1=Meryl|date=28 January 2020|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref> This was followed by attempts to threaten the protesters. On 28 January 2020, an armed man entered the Shaheen Bagh protest site, climbed the stage, and threatened people to stop the agitation; he was later overpowered by protesters.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/armed-man-threatens-shaheen-bagh-protesters-overpowered/article30676177.ece|title=Armed man threatens Shaheen Bagh protesters, overpowered|date=28 January 2020|work=The Hindu|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref> On 1 February, a [[Hindutva|Hindu fundamentalist]] entered the barricaded area and fired a gun into the air near the stage; he was taken into police custody.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scroll.in/video/951843/i-am-kapil-gujjar-listen-to-the-man-who-fired-a-gun-at-shaheen-bagh-explain-his-reason|title='I am Kapil Gujjar': Listen to the man who fired a gun at Shaheen Bagh explain his reason|date=1 February 2020|work=The Scroll|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/india-news-man-opens-fire-near-shaheen-bagh-protest-site/346608|title='...Sirf Hinduon Ki Chalegi': Man Opens Fire Near Shaheen Bagh Protest Site|date=1 February 2020|work=The Outlook India|accessdate=1 February 2020|publisher=The India Today}}</ref> The incident happened two days after a Hindu fundamentalist shot and injured a student protester in the presence of police near [[Jamia Millia Islamia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/shots-fired-at-delhis-shaheen-bagh-days-after-jamia-shooting-man-taken-into-custody-2482733.html|title=Man Opens Fire in Delhi's Shaheen Bagh 2 Days After Jamia Shooting, Shouts 'Only Hindus Will Rule'|date=1 February 2020|work=The News18|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/in-2nd-incident-man-opens-fire-in-shaheen-bagh-detained/1723624|title=In 2nd incident, man opens fire in Shaheen Bagh; detained|date=1 February 2020|work=The Outlook India|accessdate=1 February 2020|publisher=The India Today}}</ref> The alleged perpetrator of the Jamia incident had made various threatening and hateful social media posts, including one in which he threatened to convert \"Shaheen Bagh into Jallianwala Bagh\", the [[Jallianwala Bagh massacre|site of a massacre]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://in.news.yahoo.com/gunman-behind-jamia-shooting-123730614.html|title=Who is the gunman behind Jamia shooting?|date=30 January 2020|work=Yahoo|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref> On 2 February 2020, the [[Election Commission of India]] transferred Chinmoy Biswal, the then deputy commissioner of police (DCP) for [[South East Delhi district|South East Delhi]], citing the multiple shooting incidents in the Jamia area, which was an election polling area.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/ec-transfers-dcp-south-east-chinmoy-biswal-after-jamia-shaheen-bagh-firing-incidents-1642642-2020-02-02|title=EC transfers Delhi Police DCP Chinmoy Biswal after Jamia, Shaheen Bagh firing incidents|date=2 February 2020|work=The India Today|accessdate=2 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Impact of coronavirus pandemic ==\nFollowing the spread of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in India|coronavirus in India]] in 2020, the ''[[Press Trust of India]]'' reported that the women at Shaheen Bagh had said that \"the protesters were being provided with masks and hand sanitisers and there was no need to be scared.\"<ref name=\":20\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/coronavirus-outbreak-curb-on-gatherings-over-coronavirus-applies-to-shaheen-bagh-delhi-chief-ministe-2195819|title=Curb On Gatherings Over Coronavirus Applies To Shaheen Bagh, Arvind Kejriwal Clarifies|last=|first=|date=17 March 2020|editor-last=Sanyal|editor-first=Anindita|work=The NDTV|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> However, the [[Chief Minister of Delhi]] made it clear that restrictions were in place in Delhi as per the [[Epidemic Diseases Act, 1897]] and this applied to protests too. Schools, colleges, malls, weekly markets, cinema halls and gatherings of more than 50 people have been banned in Delhi.<ref name=\":20\" /> The Chief Minister made it clear that those who did not comply with the Act would be punished.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-51907173|title=Why coronavirus may halt months-long India protest|date=2020-03-16|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-17|language=en-GB}}</ref> However, the coordinators stated that \"the order of shut down has come for entertainment services, while Shaheen Bagh is agitation and fight for survival\" and that only a Supreme Court order could get them to move.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/shaheen-bagh-protesters-to-be-removed-as-coronavirus-precautionary-measure/article31089679.ece|title=Shaheen Bagh protesters to be removed as precautionary measure|last=Awasthi|first=Prashasti|date=17 March 2020|publisher=The Hindu|work=The Businessline|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> As a precautionary measure the protesters planned for a \"controlled gathering\".<ref name=\"HT SBagh 1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/shaheen-bagh-protest-on-despite-health-risk/story-myJmOAhQItEqxh73i0XSiI.html|title=Shaheen Bagh protest on despite health risk|date=2020-03-14|work=The Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nThe protest followed the \"[[Janata Curfew]]\", a self-imposed [[curfew]] annoucned by the Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi]] on 22 March 2020,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/4-hour-cap-kids-and-elderly-barred-no-mics-coronavirus-tweaks-to-shaheen-bagh-protests-2545191.html|title=4-Hour Cap, Kids and Elderly Barred, No Mics: Coronavirus Tweaks to Shaheen Bagh Protests|last=|first=|date=21 March 2020|website=News18|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> by reducing the number of protesters to 5 and symbolically leaving behind cots and sandals by other protesters at the site in solidarity.<ref name=\"SB corona outbreak\">{{cite news |title=As Shaheen Bagh Sticks to 5 Protester Limit, Vigilante Attacks Site With Petrol Bomb |url=https://thewire.in/communalism/petrol-bomb-shaheen-bagh-janata-curfew |work=The Wire|accessdate=24 March 2020 |date=22 March 2020}}</ref> However, a complete [[lockdown]] was imposed in Delhi by Chief Minister [[Arvind Kejriwal]] from 23 to 31 March 2020, folowing which the protesters were removed by the Delhi police on 24 March 2020.<ref name=\"100days\"/> It was reported that the police arrested the protesters who were present there as they refused to end the protest and leave the site.<ref name=\"100days\"/><ref>{{cite news |title=Shaheen Bagh protest site cleared by police as Delhi goes under coronavirus lockdown |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/delhi-lockdown-coronavirus-shaheen-bagh-protest-cleared-1658927-2020-03-24 |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=The India Today |date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" heights=\"120\">\nFile:No Cash No Paytm No Account Shaheen Bagh Protests 1 Jan 2020.jpg\nFile:Volunteers getting books and posters for protestors shaheen bagh new delhi 7 jan 2020.jpg\nFile:No CCA graffiti on a police barridcade in New Delhi 8 Jan 2020.jpg\nFile:Shaheen Bagh on the eve of New Year.jpg\nFile:Standing in solidarity with AMU JNU Jamia Shaheen Bagh anti CAA NRC police brutality protests New Delhi 8 Jan 2020.jpg\nFile:Slogan against ABVP at Shaheen Bagh protests 11 Jan 2020.jpg\nFile:The colour I belong to is tricolour not saffron At Shaheen Bagh protests 11 Jan 2020.jpg\nFile:A photo wall curated by the youth of Jamia Miliia Islamia University 28 Jan 2020 at Shaheen Bagh protests.jpg\nFile:Footbridge shaheen bagh covered in anti nrc caa posters new delhi 7 jan 2020.jpg\nFile:Handmade posters at Shaheen Bagh protests.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|India|Politics|Law|History|Freedom of speech|Society}}\n* [[Protests of 2019]]\n*[[Irom Chanu Sharmila]]\n* [[2020 Women's March]]\n* [[2019\u201320 French pension reform strike]]\n* [[Yellow vests movement]]\n*[[No NRC Movement]].\n\n== Footnotes ==\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Bibliography ==\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ih_yQxp